‘Today with Me’, mural inspired by, and symbolic of Christ’s crucifixion. 
🌲
The Kauri trees represent the crosses that Jesus and the two criminals were crucified upon. Kauri chosen for their tall, straight structure and to relate this event in a way unique to the native flora of Aotearoa.
🐑
The title comes from the conversation between the ‘believing’ criminal and Jesus response to him that ‘today you will be with me in paradise’. 
🌳
There are other symbols interwoven in this allegorical artwork, and I hope meaning that will become apparent to many viewers over time. 
❤️
I feel very privileged to have been given the opportunity to paint on this wall, grateful to the three wonderful women that worked alongside to complete the painting... and also a sense of achievement that I didn’t freak out being up such a tall ladder!!
🌺
I hope you all have a safe, reflective and restful Easter. Xx

Quando em 2018, entrei na Universidade, por sorte, acabei conhecendo grandes amigos que tenho comigo até hoje.
@valentinamussi_ foi uma delas. Certamente, o que eu não esperava era logo conhecer os amigos dos meus amigos e de certa forma, me tornar algo próximo a eles.
Esse foi o caso de @biasantarosa_ . Cinheci a Bia através de Valentina, que consequentemente me fez conhecer o trabalho de Bia e me trazer a pergunta que move esse novo projeto que eu carinhosamente chamei de como se fosse:
Como tudo começou pra Bia? Qual foi o motivo dela ter começado a criar?
Bom, eu não vejo a hora de responder essa pergunta e poder compartilhar com vocês.
.
Bia Santarosa é uma das convidadas pro projeto "como se fosse" onde nós dois faremos uma peça juntos em um vídeo onde ela conta um pouco do começo, como se ainda fossemos crianças.

It didn't take long after I started my street art project that I began getting push back from people. A few upset messages that I was going against the stay at home orders (true) and by putting art out, I was encouraging people to do the same (debatable) and thus putting people in danger (I could not disagree more.) Just irritated that I had the nerve to be creating art during a pandemic. Arguably, I felt art is what we could all use more of. It was the first time that I had gotten negative feedback like that for my art, and it immediately signaled to me that I was doing something important, and that I should ABSOLUTELY keep doing it. Thankfully the positive messages far outweighed the negative, but unfortunately those negative ones are the ones that you spend more energy on. 

On one particular day I got a slew of awful messages from a young man who was losing his mind that I was doing street art. He was irate I had used the hashtag #graffiti and berated me, my art, and my character over the course of several hours. It was amusing to say the least. I even offered to meet him for coffee- my treat. Surprise, surprise... he declined the offer. But in that fiery exchange of hate messages, he said I was a disgrace to the graffiti and street art community and my stuff was yuppie eyesore garbage. I didn't waste a second before heading into my studio to paint this one as a tribute to one of my first haters, and I've used the hashtag #yuppieeyesoregarbage ever since. 

Don't let the jerkwads get you down. If anything, let them inspire you. They're just as important to the journey as the people who cheer you on. And for that, I have immense gratitude. 🙏❤
.

Vita e Morte – Herbert Baglione  

Via delle Conce, 13 - Roma, Italia
Latitude: 41.874080 | Longitude: 12.478001 

Lo so, lo so… lo scorso venerdì ho saltato un appuntamento della rubrica #streetartdenoantri.

 Sono settimane molto intense con tanti nuovi progetti personali e lavorativi che piano piano stanno prendendo forma e questo ahimè mi porta ad avere meno tempo libero.  

Ma per farmi perdonare torno oggi con un’opera davvero incredibile! Siamo ancora una volta al quartiere Ostiense, all’ombra della Piramide Cestia e il nome dell’opera è “Vita e Morte” dello street artist brasiliano Herbert Baglione. 

Siamo sul muro esterno della storica falegnameria Blasi e con questo murales l’artista  rappresenta figure umane distorte che evocano l’immagine di un mondo alienato da sé, distratto e confuso.  

Il significato dell’opera è una critica alla società contemporanea. I personaggi, infatti, si trovano in un mare scuro e denso in cui galleggiano da soli e lontani gli uni dagli altri. L'artista usa questa metafora per dirci che nella società in cui viviamo siamo tutti quanti individui isolati e distratti, spesso sovrastati da una nube di pensieri grigi.   

Se pubblichi foto di murales presenti a Roma usa l’hashtag #streetartdenoantri e sarò felice di ricondividerti nelle mie storie!

Olive tree leaf inspired mural with the silver leaf applied. This mural is super close to my heart. It was done in South Africa for my sister in law's (@drdebbienorval) clinic. Olive trees symbolize healing, wisdom and peace and are a representation of her amazing work to restore youth, beauty and confidence for her patients. For this mural, I started with a series of blue glazed washes in the background and then overlaid the olive leaf design on top. It's all hand painted with added distressed silver leaf to really give it dimension and shine. I was SO honored to create a mural for her clinic as a representation of her business and work.

Eunírico, 2021 por Farmer Teut

No que diz respeito aos sonhos, longe da realidade podemos ser muitas coisas. 

O Onirismo nada mais é do que o estado mental difuso, cheio de alucinações visuais de interação entre o real e o irreal, mesmo estando acordado.

De acordo com o artista, o obra é "a representação da auto-reflexão  e construção de imagem enquanto ser humano. Uma busca interna pelo entendimento de quem sou, o que busco e qual o meu propósito."

E aí, quem é você no onírico?

"Brave Wall" by Katerina Voronina @voroninakate and @emily_eldridge_art in Kooperation mit @urbanation_berlin und @amnestydeutschland zum Internationalen Frauentag am 8. März 2021 in der Gitschiner Str. 64-67 in Berlin-Kreuzberg.
For project "Brave Wall" to celebrate the #InternationalWomensDay, in memoriam to Marielle Franco, who was a Brazilian politician, sociologist, feminist, socialist, and women rights activist.
On 14 March 2018 Franco and her driver were killed by two murderers in another vehicle in Rio de Janeiro. Franco had been an outspoken critic of police brutality and extrajudicial killings.
Fotografiert am 30. März 2021 von Bernd Sauer-Diete.

" Fonte de Bênçãos "

Mural que fiz na comunidade  da Mauro no bairro da Saúde  na zona sul  de São Paulo convidado pelo meu amigo Jota Bandeira.

Já se passaram  quase 23 anos pintandos na ruas de diversas cidades  e regiões, e cada vez mais tenho uma certeza.
 
 A arte é  uma poderosa ferramenta  de transformação e  transmutação de energias. Alegrando  vezes com sutileza, vezes escancaradamente a realidade de todos que vivem ao entorno e por  ali passam.

Sentir toda a receptividade, alegria e gratidão  de todas as pessoas por onde  deixo minha arte é algo realmente  verdadeiro  e gratificante. 

Agradeço  a todos artistas que contribuem  dia a dia colorindo a vidas das pessoas. Passando mensagens  de paz e questionando nossas realidades  dia a dia.

[GRAFITE] O grafiteiro Cranio (Fabio de Oliveira Parnaiba) espalha sua arte pelos muros desde 1998. Hoje em dia, suas obras podem ser vistas não somente em São Paulo, mas em várias cidades mundo afora. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Sua marca registrada é a figura de um indígena azul, que aparece em meio à cacofonia das ruas e avenidas. O artista se vale desse personagem para intervir criticamente em temas contemporâneos como identidade, meio ambiente, violência, corrupção política e consumismo. Seus grafites contrariam a narrativa colonialista que recusa a cultura e as tradições dos povos nativos e que apresenta o indígena como alguém isolado do restante da sociedade. A arte de Cranio subverte esses valores ao escolher para protagonista um grupo social historicamente excluído.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Pichador na adolescência, Cranio mudou de rumo mais tarde. Sobre a diferença entre picho e grafite, explica: “O grafite é uma forma de linguagem mais elaborada. É feita, na maioria das vezes, durante o dia e com autorização”. A maior referência do artista é a zona norte paulistana, onde cresceu. Essa parte da cidade tem destaque na história do grafite por ser um dos primeiros lugares onde a arte urbana apareceu com força, e ainda hoje se mantém viva.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
👉 Fonte das imagens: @cranioartes 
📚 Sugestão de leitura: Maurília Gomes, José Carvalheiro. “Graffiti e crítica social: uma análise discursiva da figura do ‘índio’ na arte de Cranio”. Disponível em: 
http://ojs.labcom-ifp.ubi.pt/index.php/eikon/article/view/692

On our way to Kansas, we stayed overnight in Ft. Smith. I've never visited this small town in Western Arkansas before, had so had some exploring to do before departing.
Unfortunately, the city like so many other small cities in the United States has economic challenges. It appeared that one out of every four buildings in downtown were vacant. 
However officials are making the best of it by spicing up city center with vibrant murals and a very cute little hop on/hop off streetcar shown in these photos. These were delightful surprises to behold. There is also an art gallery and music pub in town.

[wip] Rénovation de peintures décoratives naturalistes sur les boiseries d’un salon du XVIIIe siècle.
.
Les décorations à l’origine ont quasiment disparu avec le temps, quelques touches de peintures suggéraient des formes et volutes qui m’ont servi de base de travail.
.
Première étape d’un long projet qui s’étalera sur l’année. Une bonne phase de recherches a été nécessaire pour s’approcher de l’esprit de l’époque et ensuite me permettre repartir de zéro pour les remettre à neuf.
.
Ici je ne fais que les panneaux décoratifs, le client a le courage de s’occuper lui même du reste des boiseries ! 💪
.

Tonight @9pm EST we sit down with contemporary artist and designer @Marlobro to learn how he's moving through creativity during a time of uncertainty. 
.
Marlo known professionally as MARLOBRO, is an American Contemporary Artist and designer. Who got his start by working with his cousin and founder of Detroit VS Everybody by Tommey Walker and linking up with members of Finally Famous which ultimatly lead to working on mixtape artworks and branding for  Big Sean's early indie career. 
.
He began as a graffiti artist, moving on to studying industrial design at WSU (Wayne state university), and now makes acrylic paintings on canvas and large scale mural paintings. He also collaborates commercially, predominantly on promotional materials, and also clothing, music production and other forms of branding. 
.
His work is exhibited in galleries, outdoors in local and international environments, you can find his work displayed on 1XRUN, PLAYGROUND DETROIT, MURALS IN THE MARKET and avidly collected by individuals. He lives and works in Detroit, Michigan.
.
.
.
.

#iaccidentallyfoundoutthat Houston has an underground pedestrian tunnel system. 

The tunnel is 20 feet underground and runs seven miles, linking 95 city blocks.  The tunnel originally connected two cinemas in the city center, but now connects major city buildings, restaurants and retail stores. 

Хьюстон – самый крупный город штата Техас и четвертый по численности населения город в США. 

Хьюстон - промышленный и транспортный центр Техаса.
Нефтяная и газовая промышленность, один из крупнейших портов в мире, крупнейший в мире Техасский медицинский центр и, конечно же, знаменитый центр управления полетами NASA и космический центр - все здесь. 🚀🧑‍🚀

А мурал нарисован Марио Фигероа-младшим, @gonzo247 
Фреска является результатом инициативы "Houston Is Inspiried", выдвинутой Бюро конференций и бизнеса Большого Хьюстона, чтобы подчеркнуть кулинарную и художественную сцену Хьюстона.

Jolie découverte de la superbe Exposition à ciel ouvert, afin de rendre l'Art accessible à tous. 
Avec la fermeture des Musées depuis plus d'un an à cause de la crise sanitaire et de la Covid-19, le Projet Murséum a été imaginé et concrétisé à l'initiative de l'Artiste Street Art Masha, afin de faire découvrir des magnifiques Œuvres Street Art, réalisées par plusieurs Street Artistes Talentueux, sur les murs à découvrir dans la ville de Lyon @mashamagosia 
Superbe Illustration et beau collage original au dessus d'un digicode, représentant un joli Poignard dessiné en noir et blanc.

El fabuloso Gota de Plata , fondo de mil fotos de graduación 🤣😂.

El Auditorio Gota de Plata es un auditorio ubicado en el Parque David Ben Gurión en Pachuca de Soto, en el estado de Hidalgo,  México.Cuenta con 14 000 m² de construcción y tiene capacidad para 2000 espectadores.
Se sitúa en la cabecera sur del parque y dada su posición, actúa como remate visual del mar de colores, efecto realizado por el mosaico Homenaje a la Mujer del Mundo de Byron Gálvez Avilés.

Les comparto el video del proyecto en el que estuve hace  unos días, pintando en la playita. 

La historia de “El Morro”(nombre del gatito) forma parte de una familia que les recuerda el amor y compañía que se tenían el y la persona que se nos adelantó de este plano. 

Me siento muy emocionado cuando pintó historias de familias, anécdotas y ese amor que fluye en sus corazones. 

Abrazamos la vida y honremos la muerte. 

Gracias por seguir confiandome sus historias para plasmarlos en muros, gracias por valorar mi trabajo.

Ruth Bader Ginsberg (15 March 1933 - 18 September 2020) New York City, USA.

Justice Ginsberg was a history-making jurist on the US Supreme Court, a feminist icon and American national treasure.

Ginsburg became only the second woman ever to serve as a justice on the nation's highest court. On and off the court, she was a lifelong advocate of gender equality, fond of joking that there would be enough women on the nine-seat Supreme Court "when there are nine".

The 7-foot-tall, 650-pound statue was unveiled last week at City Point Brooklyn, a mixed-use development about a half mile away from the Brooklyn Bridge.

It was created by Australian artists Gillie and Marc, who got Ginsburg's approval for the statue before she died in September 2020 from complications of metastatic pancreas cancer.

倪匡 // 「喜歡怎麼過日子，可以憑借自己的意思。同樣美麗。」

「音樂是沒有高低級之分，有一些人推崇古典音樂，不知是基於什麼樣的滑稽心態。今日稱之為古典音樂者，昔年也一樣是流行音樂；今日之流行音樂，若干年之後，也就成了古典音樂。」

「你愛看的書，就是你該看的書。書海浩瀚，總有你愛看的，那就看。不愛看的，別浪費生命。若看了古文就惹氣，那就看今文。看書的主要目的，是在看的過程得到快樂，享受閱讀帶來的樂趣，那樂趣是越看越濃的。十年業余讀古文，所得閱讀樂趣之多，肯定非同小可。」

「古語叫『授人以柄』，即把劍給別人刺自己，好不智。」

Ni Kuang, is a Hong Kong-American novelist and screenwriter. He has written over 300 Chinese-language wuxia and science fiction novels, and more than 400 film scripts.

Aloha everyone! This week, we're featuring a small town from Kauai, the northernmost island in Hawaii. This wall honors Hanapepe, "Kauai's Biggest Little Town."⁠
.⁠
Known as the art capital of the island, Hanapepe is a small community that boasts a lot of creative talent in its population of just under 3,000 locals. Learn all about this community and some of the traditions that inspired this design in the full blog post at smalltownwalls.com (link in bio!)⁠
.⁠
For this town especially, I am SO grateful for the information made available by local native Hawaiian artisans, historians, and journalists. Mahalo to @aloha.authentic, Ho’okulena LLC,  and @hanahoumag for the informative content you share. As always, all resources are linked at the bottom of the full post for further exploration 😎⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
